<inglise> Council Regulation (EEC) No 525/92 of 25 February 1992 on temporary compensation for the consequences of the situation in Yugoslavia on transport of some fresh fruit and vegetables from Greece </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 525/92 Jugoslaavias tekkinud olukorra tagaj&auml;rgede t&otilde;ttu teatavate Kreekast p&auml;rit v&auml;rskete puu- ja k&ouml;&ouml;giviljade veol makstava ajutise h&uuml;vitise kohta 25. veebruar 1992 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular Article 43 (2) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artikli 43 l&otilde;iget 2, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust (2) ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the state of war that has arisen in Yugoslavia in 1991 has caused sudden and prolonged blockage of the routes normally and regularly used for transport of certain agricultural products; whereas such is the case for the road and rail transport of fresh fruit and vegetables from Greece to Member States other than Italy; </inglise>
<eesti> Jugoslaavias 1991. aastal tekkinud s&otilde;jaseisukord on p&otilde;hjustanud teatavate p&otilde;llumajandussaaduste veoks tavaliselt ja korrap&auml;raselt kasutatud teede ootamatu ja pikemaajalise blokaadi; selline on olukord Kreekast p&auml;rit v&auml;rskete puu- ja k&ouml;&ouml;giviljade maantee- ja raudteeveol teistesse liikmesriikidesse kui Itaalia; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas this exceptional situation, unprecedented since the common agricultural policy was introduced, is liable, given its duration, the highly perishable nature of the products and the need to ensure that quality standards are observed throughout the distribution process, to have damaging consequences on the Greek fruit and vegetable sector, which forms an important part of that Member State's economy; </inglise>
<eesti> sellel erandlikul olukorral, mis on p&auml;rast &uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitika kehtestamist enneolematu, ja pidades silmas selle kestust, k&otilde;nealuste toodete eriti kiiret riknemist ja vajadust tagada kvaliteedistandardite j&auml;rgimine kogu turustusprotsessi jooksul, on kahjulikud tagaj&auml;rjed Kreeka puu- ja k&ouml;&ouml;giviljasektorile, mis moodustab olulise osa k&otilde;nealuse liikmesriigi majandusest; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the operators concerned must be given temporary assistance to permit them to adapt as rapidly as possible to the new situation; whereas none of the existing instruments of common organization of the sector can be used to provide such assistance; </inglise>
<eesti> asjaomastele ettev&otilde;tjatele tuleb anda ajutist abi, mis v&otilde;imaldaks neil uue olukorraga v&otilde;imalikult ruttu kohaneda; sellise abi andmiseks ei saa kasutada &uuml;htegi asjaomase sektori &uuml;hise korralduse olemasolevat vahendit; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas special temporary financial compensation should therefore be granted, corresponding to the increased road and rail transport costs incurred in avoiding Yugoslavia, for consignments made by refrigerated lorry or wagon in 1991 from Greece to other Member States except Italy of fresh fruit and vegetables referred to in Article 1 of Council Regulation (EEC) No 1035/72 of 18 May 1972 on the common organization of the market in fruit and vegetables (3); whereas compensation under this measure should be limited to ECU 4 million; </inglise>
<eesti> seep&auml;rast tuleb 1991. aastal Kreekast teistesse liikmesriikidesse kui Itaaliasse k&uuml;lmutusautode v&otilde;i k&uuml;lmvagunitega veetavate n&otilde;ukogu 18. mai 1972. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1035/72 (puu- ja k&ouml;&ouml;giviljaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta (3)) artiklis 1 osutatud v&auml;rskete puu- ja k&ouml;&ouml;giviljade saadetiste puhul m&auml;&auml;rata erakorraline ajutine rahaline h&uuml;vitis, mis vastab suurenenud maantee- v&otilde;i raudteeveokuludele, mis tekivad Jugoslaaviast &uuml;mbers&otilde;itmise t&otilde;ttu; k&otilde;nealune h&uuml;vitis peaks piirduma 4 miljoni ek&uuml;&uuml;ga; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas this measure aims to fulfil the objectives of Article 39 of the Treaty; whereas it should therefore be financed by the Guarantee Section of the European Agriculture Guidance and Guarantee Fund (EAGGF), </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;nealuse meetme eesm&auml;rk on t&auml;ita asutamislepingu artikli 39 eesm&auml;rke; seep&auml;rast peaks seda rahastama Euroopa P&otilde;llumajanduse Arendus- ja Tagatisfondi (EAGGF) tagatisrahastu, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Financial compensation shall be granted, for the additional costs incurred by the need to avoid Yugoslavia, on consignments of fresh fruit and vegetables referred to in Article 1 of Regulation (EEC) No 1035/72 made in 1991 by refrigerated lorry or wagon from Greece to Member States other than Italy. </inglise>
<eesti> Kreekast teistesse liikmesriikidesse kui Itaaliasse k&uuml;lmutusautode v&otilde;i k&uuml;lmvagunitega veetavate m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1035/72 artiklis 1 osutatud v&auml;rskete puu- ja k&ouml;&ouml;giviljade saadetiste puhul m&auml;&auml;ratakse Jugoslaaviast &uuml;mbers&otilde;itmise t&otilde;ttu tekkinud lisakulutuste jaoks rahaline h&uuml;vitis. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The Community expenditure estimated as necessary for the payment of the financial compensation provided for in Article 1 amounts to ECU 4 million. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;henduse arvestuslikud kulutused artikliga 1 etten&auml;htud rahalise h&uuml;vitise maksmiseks on 4 miljonit ek&uuml;&uuml;d. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The budget authority shall determine the appropriations available for each financial year. </inglise>
<eesti> Eelarvep&auml;devad institutsioonid m&auml;&auml;ravad igal eelarveaastal kasutatavad assigneeringud. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> Financial compensation shall be paid to the consignor on presentation to the competent authorities of documents substantiating his claim. </inglise>
<eesti> Rahaline h&uuml;vitis makstakse kaubasaatjale, kui ta esitab p&auml;devale asutusele oma n&otilde;uet t&otilde;endavad dokumendid. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission, acting in accordance with the procedure referred to in Article 4, shall determine what documents are required to that end. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon m&auml;&auml;rab selleks n&otilde;utavad dokumendid artiklis 4 osutatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission shall, in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 33 of Regulation (EEC) No 1035/72, adopt rules for application of this Regulation, and in particular on the amount of the financial compensation. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon v&otilde;tab m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1035/72 artiklis 33 s&auml;testatud korras vastu k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse rakenduseeskirjad ja eelk&otilde;ige rahalise h&uuml;vitise suuruse. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> The measures provided for under this Regulation shall be considered as intervention intended to stabilize the agricultural markets within the meaning of Article 3 of Council Regulation (EEC) No 729/70 of 21 April 1970 on the financing of the common agricultural policy (4). </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud meetmeid k&auml;sitatakse sekkumisena, mille eesm&auml;rk on p&otilde;llumajandusturgude stabiliseerimine &uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitika rahastamist k&auml;sitleva n&otilde;ukogu 21. aprilli 1970. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 279/70 (4) artiklis 3 m&auml;&auml;ratletud t&auml;henduses. </eesti>
<inglise> These measures shall be financed by the EAGGF Guarantee Section. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;nealuseid meetmeid rahastab EAGGFi tagatisrahastu. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force from the third day following that of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kolmandal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 25 February 1992. </inglise>
